                    Uniforms in hospitals serve not only to
                    maintain a professional appearance but
                    also to promote cleanliness and hygiene.
                    They are often made of breathable and
                    easy-to-clean materials, ensuring that
                    healthcare workers can carry out their duties
                    comfortably while adhering to strict infection
                    control protocols. Additionally, uniforms help
                    patients and visitors easily identify different
                    staff members, fostering clear
                    communication and trust in the medical
                    team.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Overall, hospital uniforms play a crucial role
                    in the healthcare environment, contributing to
                    both the functionality and professionalism of
                    medical staff. Properly designed and maintained
                    uniforms enhance the overall patient experience
                    and support the vital work carried out by
                    healthcare professionals.
                </p>
                <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ContactUs" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
